<Content>Wonderful hotel in a good location. Just returned from a three day break to Barcelona staying at the Catalonia Bernia Hotel. Looks old and historical from the outside with a modern interia.The hotel was within a few minutes walk of the centre e.g. Las Ramblas and we were delighted with the service and hospitality we received. Everywhere in the hotel was beautiful and clean. The rooms were of a good 4* standard and the breakfasts were fantastic! There were fresh, white towels each day and bathrooms were super clean.We certainly were pleased with our stay and if ever we return to the city would be happy to stay there again. P.S. The staff were friendly and helpful too, although one young receptionist did forget to order us a taxi and the one we picked up outside the hotel began taking us to the wrong station making it a more expensive and nail biting journey as we nearly missed our connecting transport. However we feel partly to blame for not speaking Spanish! This was the only minor fault of the entire weekend.Booking 2 day tickets on the Touristica bus certainly let us make the most of the city and we would recommend this if you want to make the most of your stay without walking your legs off.This also allows you to go out for lunch or tapas outside the city centre where good three course lunches can be eaten with wine for 10 euros. These are typically Spanish restaurants where you get a limited choice but excellent quality and value.review from Chesterfield in Derbyshire. 
