<Content>Fair to middling I decided on this hotel partly as a result of reading recomendations on this site. My reason for adding this review was because I seemed to feel differently about this hotel than most. People seemed to love it or loathe it! I on the other hand thought that it was just ok. I do think it's a little expensive for what you get, and rather lacking in character. This being said, it is scrupulously clean, the staff are efficient if not overly welcoming (but no compliants on that front) and the breakfast offers a very good variety of fruits, hams, chesses, yoghurt, tortillas, sausage, bacon etc. My breakfast was included, and I managed to get a drink at the bar on 2 occasions although the bar wasn't patronised by many. All in all we encountered no problems with hotel, it just became clear wandering around Barcelona that there appeared to be much more interesting and cheaper hotels all over the city. This was a last minute booking for me, so all in all it was fine, but I'd advise others to maybe spend a little more time researching hotels than I did. One very strong feature of this hotel is the location which is excellent, one major let down is if you don't get a terrace room (there are very few) there is no outside space in which to just sit and relax. 
